class Solution {
    public int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        int i = 5;
        while (n / i >= 1) {
            count += n / i;
            i *= 5;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution counts the number of factors of 5 in n!, as each trailing zero is created by a factor of 2 and a factor of 5, and there are usually more factors of 2 than 5. It iterates through powers of 5, adding the count of each power to the total count of trailing zeroes.

